The paper deals with incentive compatibility in dynamic systems, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of layered payments over time suggests a control systems (cs.SY) approach. The optimization of social welfare over linear control laws suggests a focus on mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the use of rational agents and the consideration of market power balance suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) perspective.
